{"id":"math140-critical_pt120-ap001","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Applications of Derivatives","subtopic":"Profit maximization","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Profit is P(x) = {a}x^2 + {b}x + {c}. Find the production level x that maximizes profit and compute that maximum profit.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":-5,"max":-1},"b":{"type":"int","min":15,"max":50},"c":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":100}},"answer_expr":"critical_pt120","steps":["P'(x) = {two_a}x + {b}. Set P'(x) = 0.","x* = -{b}/{two_a} = {x_star}.","Maximum profit = P({x_star}) = {fx_star}."],"tags":["business-calculus","profit-maximization","critical-point","optimization"]}
